and development of cadets  Members of the Council are selected from parents of cadets in the upper three classes  The Parents Council is overseen by the President and the Vice President Elect  There are four main committees in the Council  Activities  Communications  Society of Friends and Family and Recruiting  Presidents Co Presidents  Rob and Cheryl Hughes hughesvmipc gmail com Colin Hughes   Class of 2016  703  569 1930 Co Vice Presidents  Ray   Michelle Lancaster Rlancaster239 windstream net John Lancaster   Class of 2017  864  415 0666 Activities Committee Activities Chair  John   Cindy Borchick borchicks gmail com John Borchick   Class of 2017  570  277 0344 Activities Co Vice Chairs Dennis   Barbara Carter dtodd64 cox net Ethan Zebron   Class of 2016  540  722 2909 Communications Committee Communications Chair Co Chairs  Parks   Mary Ann Taylor Maryanntaylor75 msn com Paige Taylor   Class of 2016  703  350 1913 Communications Co Vice Chair  Alison Ahmed alisonjahmed aol com Zach Regen   Class of 2017  703  244 8864  Society of Friends   Family Society of Friends and Family Chairs  Randy   Debbie de Steuben ddesteuben gmail com Chris de Steuben   Class of 2016  703  729 9811 Recruiting Committee Recruiting Co Chairs  Tynan   Debbie Dawson VABasket aol com Emily Dawson   Class of 2017  703  724 4178 Recruiting Vice Chairs  Melissa and Marc Nobile stillhouse hughes net Emma Nobile   Class of 2017  540  364 3699  804  639 5558 Parents Council New Parents Council New Parents Council New      Parents Council The Parents Council was established to provide a forum for the interchange of ideas and information between parents  cadets and Institute officials  create an organization to formulate and administer plans and projects  bring the parents of cadets into closer association with VMI  aid in the growth and development of the VMI Foundation  and to assist the Institute in providing for the welfare and development of cadets  Members of the Council are selected from 